<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-638-937  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 638 937.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Nov 26 1990 v7 n48 p19(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ameritrust banking on distributed net. (platform automationnetwork)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Ameritrust Corp is implementing a three-tier distributedprocessing network architecture that the bank holding companyhopes will increase sales and improve customer service.andO;Ameritrust is working under a special contract with DEC to obtainhardware and customized software that supports the architecture.andO;The company will link microcomputers and teller terminals viaEthernet to a DEC VAXserver 3100 that provides network file andprint services.andP;  There will also be a link to an IBM 3090mainframe computer.andP;  The network will link 220 branches in Ohio,Indiana and Michigan.andP;  Customer service representatives will beable to open new accounts electronically and merge data fromdifferent data bases.andP;  Users will also be able to usemicrocomputer- or server-based applications to design customizedsavings and loan programs.andP;  Various aspects of the network arediscussed in detail.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ameritrust Corp. (Communication systems)Digital Equipment Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    AMTR; DEC; IBM.andO;Product:   DEC VAXserver 3100 (File server) (Business use)IBM 3090 (Mainframe computer) (Business use).andO;Topic:     Network ArchitectureDistributed ProcessingBankingEthernetBranch Banking.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Computers and functions supported on Ameritrust's network. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>